Organizations
==============================================================================================
Name: Drug Enforcement Administration
Kind: Government law enfocement agency
Location: United States
History: The DEA was established on July 1, 1973 by Reorganization Plan No. 2 of 1973 which was signed
	 by President Richard Nixon on July 28, 1973. The plan proposed the creation of a single
	 federal agency to enforce federal drug laws and consolidate and coordinated the government's
	 drug control activities. Congress accepted the proposal and the Bureau of Narcotics and
	 Dangerous Drugs and the Office of Drug Abuse Law Enforcement merged o create the DEA. The
	 current DEA Administrator is Michele Leonhart and the current DEA Chief of Operations is 	   Thomas M. Harrigan.
Contact Info: http://www.justice.gov/dea/contactinfo.htm
Embedded Images:http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/54/US-DrugEnforcementAdministration-Seal.svg/600px-US-DrugEnforcementAdministration-Seal.svg.png
Embedded Videos: http://www.youtube.com/embed/dSUGY8qV6Jc
Social Networks: None
External Links: http://www.justice.gov/dea/
Related Crises: Bath Salts
Related People: Michele Leonhart
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Name: Department of Defense
Kind: Government agency
Location: The Pentagon, Virginia, United States
History: The US Congress created the War Department in 1789 and the Navy Department in 1798. In 1945
	 President Truman proposed the creation of a unified department of state defense, citing both
	 wasteful military spending and inter-departmental conflicts. In 1947, President Truman signed
	 the National Security Act of 1947, which set up a unified military command known as the
	 National Military Establishment. The National Military Establishment was renamed the
	 Department of Defense on August 10, 1949, in an amendment to the original 1947 law.
Contact Info: http://www.defense.gov/landing/comment.aspx
Embedded Images: http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d2/The_Pentagon_US_Department_of_Defense_building.jpg/800px-The_Pentagon_US_Department_of_Defense_building.jpg
Embedded Videos: http://www.youtube.com/embed/bJ76-dVSrBc
Social Networks: None
External Links: http://www.defense.gov/
Related Crises: North Korea and Nuclear Weapons
Related People: Barack Obama, Kim Jung-un
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Name: Federal Reserve
Kind: Banking System
Location: United States
History: The Federal Reserve System was created on December 23, 1913 through the Federal Reserve Act.
	 This was in response to a series of panics, particularly the Panic of 1907 when the NYSE fell
	 almost 50% from its peak the previous year. Since then, the roles and responsibilities of the
	 Federal Reserve System have expanded and the structure has evolved. Ben Bernanke is the
	 current Chairman of the Federal Reserve System.
Contact Info: http://www.federalreserve.gov/apps/contactus/feedback.aspx?refURL=http://www.google.com/url?sa=t&rct=j&q=&esrc=s&source=web&cd=1&ved=0CGAQFjAA&url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.federalreserve.gov%2Ffeedback.cfm&ei=i5zrT9a5G42E8ATOt6DVBQ&usg=AFQjCNGRj7XZ997aEVjw_rr8kpvDD3N22Q&sig2=nFjI1YBROTyE3tyHlXnN6A
Embedded Images: http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8d/Marriner_S._Eccles_Federal_Reserve_Board_Building.jpg/800px-Marriner_S._Eccles_Federal_Reserve_Board_Building.jpg
Embedded Videos: http://www.youtube.com/embed/pQGhfQnRzYk
Social Networks: None
External Links: http://www.federalreserve.gov/
Related Crises: Global Financial Crisis
Related People: Barack Obama
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Name: United Nations
Kind: International Co-operation
Location: New York City, New York, United States
History: The United Nations was established in 1945 to replace the League of Nations, which failed to
	 prevent World War II. The main goal of the organization is to maintain international peace
	 and promote cooperation in solving international problems. The UN Conference on International
	 Organization began on April 25, 1945 with 50 governments in attendance. The UN Charter was
	 ratified on October 24, 1945 by France, the Republic of China, the Soviet Union, the United
	 States, and the United Kingdom (the five permanent members of the Security Council at the
	 time) as well as a majority of the other 46 signatories. The UN was originally based at the
	 Sperry Gyroscope Corporation's facility in Lake Success, New York, from 1946-1952, before
	 being moved to the UN Headquarters building in Manhattan. The United Nations currently has 		 193 member states.
Contact Info: http://www.un.org/en/contactus/
Embedded Images: http://www.un.org/cyberschoolbus/untour/imgunh.jpg
Embedded Videos: http://www.youtube.com/embed/bHmXZXsABm0
Social Networks: None
External Links: www.un.org
Related Crises: North Korea and Nuclear Weapons, Tibean Occupation
Related People: Barack Obama, Dalai Lama

